      "bullets": [
        {
          "details": "OpenAI has abruptly discontinued its Sora AI video platform just over a year after launch, prompting Disney to scrap a planned $1 billion investment deal involving its Marvel and Pixar IP.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            117,
            181
          ],
          "position": 1,
          "topic": "OpenAI shuts down Sora, Disney cancels $1B investment"
        },
        {
          "details": "A landmark jury verdict in Los Angeles found Meta and Google liable for designing Instagram and YouTube to be addictive to minors, awarding $6 million in damages. The ruling creates a significant legal precedent that may threaten tech platforms with broad liability for product design choices.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            56
          ],
          "position": 2,
          "topic": "Jury finds Meta and Google liable for platform design harms to minors"
        },
        {
          "details": "OpenAI is abandoning its initiative to build its own data centers, opting to shift focus to cloud partnerships with Microsoft, Amazon, and Oracle to reduce capital expenditures and appease investor concerns ahead of a planned IPO.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            68
          ],
          "position": 3,
          "topic": "OpenAI shifts strategy, abandoning proprietary data centers ahead of IPO"
        },
        {
          "details": "CERN is bypassing traditional GPUs for real-time physics filtering, instead burning highly optimized AI models directly into FPGAs and ASICs. This hardware-first approach allows for nanosecond-latency data filtering at the detector level.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            155
          ],
          "position": 4,
          "topic": "CERN optimizes AI for real-time physics by burning models into silicon"
        },
        {
          "details": "Alibaba and Baidu have announced price increases of up to 34% for key AI computing and storage services. The repricing reflects rising hardware supply-chain costs and surging demand for AI infrastructure in China.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            23,
            92
          ],
          "position": 5,
          "topic": "Alibaba and Baidu raise AI cloud prices as demand outstrips supply"
        },
        {
          "details": "Microsoft has confirmed it will continue to provide Anthropic\u2019s Claude models in M365 and GitHub Copilot for commercial customers, despite the Pentagon's decision to label Anthropic a \"supply-chain risk\" and initiate a formal off-ramp for defense use.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            50
          ],
          "position": 6,
          "topic": "Microsoft commits to keeping Claude in commercial products despite Pentagon blacklist"
        },
        {
          "details": "Wikipedia has officially prohibited editors from using AI for writing or rewriting articles to protect content integrity. The new policy restricts AI tools to basic copy editing and translation, following community concerns over AI-generated content quality.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            200
          ],
          "position": 7,
          "topic": "Wikipedia bans AI for article writing to protect content integrity"
        },
        {
          "details": "The U.S. DOJ has unsealed an indictment charging Supermicro co-founder Wally Liaw with a multi-year scheme to evade export controls. Prosecutors allege the company diverted roughly $2.5 billion in restricted AI servers containing Nvidia GPUs to China.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            19
          ],
          "position": 8,
          "topic": "Supermicro co-founder charged with $2.5B illegal export of AI servers to China"
        },
        {
          "details": "Autonomous drone manufacturer Lucid Bots secured $20 million in Series B funding to scale production. The company, which builds robots for hazardous industrial cleaning tasks, is seeing rapid commercial traction with sales approaching 1,000 units.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            195
          ],
          "position": 9,
          "topic": "Lucid Bots raises $20M to scale industrial cleaning drones"
        },
        {
          "details": "Hypura is a new inference scheduler for Apple Silicon that prevents memory-constrained Macs from crashing when running large models. It works by intelligently offloading model tensors from unified memory to NVMe storage, enabling execution of models that exceed RAM capacity.",
          "news_item_ids": [
            176
          ],
          "position": 10,
          "topic": "Hypura enables running LLMs larger than Mac RAM via NVMe streaming"
        }
      ],
      "case_id": "prod_real_summary_4w_200_strict",
      "citation_validity": 1.0,
      "curated_group_count": 10,
      "digest_id": 1,
      "digest_summary": "The tech landscape is shifting rapidly as OpenAI discontinues Sora and abandons its data center plans, leading to a scrapped $1 billion Disney partnership and a strategic pivot toward cloud infrastructure ahead of its IPO. Legal pressures are mounting, with Meta and Google found liable for addictive design, while a massive DOJ investigation accuses Supermicro of illegally exporting AI servers to China. Elsewhere, Microsoft defies a Pentagon ban on Anthropic\u2019s Claude, Wikipedia clamps down on AI-generated content, and hardware innovations from CERN and Hypura promise new breakthroughs in AI speed and accessibility.",
      "digest_title": "OpenAI Abandons Sora and Data Centers, Tech Giants Face Landmark Liability Rulings",
      "failed_processing_count": 0,
